result.execSummary:
The defendant Ivory L Holmes was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court appointed atty bill from Linda Schaefer. Court approves bill.

Defendant Ivory L Holmes in court with attorney Linda Jean Schaefer.  Defendant Ivory L Holmes in custody.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State amends Ct. 1 to Misdemeanor Bail Jumping, gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to amended Ct. 1.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty of amended Ct. 1. Court dismisses Ct. 2 but reads in for sentencing. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.
Contract for Repayment of Court-appointed Attorney Fees
Atty Schaefer asks court to reduce cash bond or convert cash bond to a signature bond. State objects to bond modification. Court denies motion to amend bond, remains in effect as previously set.

Defendant Ivory L Holmes in court, in custody.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty Gerbers indicates defendant does not qualify for PD representation. Court reviews events in file, questions defendant on how he wishes to proceed re: counsel.  Defendant to fill out form for court appointed attorney and case will then be recalled. Court recalls case at 11:25 am. Court appoints Atty Linda Schaefer to represent defendant. Atty Schaefer accepts court appointment. Atty Schaefer indicates defendant is not waiving time limits for prelim. Court sets status for 6/07/16 at 4:00 with Judge Bischel. If State can get an offer to the defense and matter can be resolved, Court is here until noon tomorrow to take a plea. If not resolved by 6/07/16, court will have prelim. set on Commissioner Moellers calendar within time limits.  Status conference scheduled for June 7, 2016 at 04:00 pm.
No contact direct or indirect with MM. To be fingerprinted and photographed before leaving Justice Center.
